body:
They should separate the toxic player and the non-toxic players. I&#039;m pretty sure that RIOT gets a thousand of reports about a toxic player everyday and once a player gets more than a certain reports for being toxic then that player would be classified as a toxic player. Now how this works is that if a player is identified as a toxic player then he only gets queues with toxic players while the non-toxic players get a separate queue. This way the toxic people can battle it out on who can be more toxic XD.

But anyway I made this post because I had a game where it was 40min + long and everyone didn&#039;t flame or trash talk or any stuff like that and the only things that the 2 teams wanted was to win the game and after the game there was no &quot;GG EZ&quot; but rather there was only  &quot;It was a tough game&quot; 
&quot;Had fun playing with you guys&quot; and I was really mesmerized by this. So if we separate the toxic players and the non-toxic players the chances of the players having a undelightful experience is lower.
